In continuation of the ongoing clearance operations of suspected Boko Haram terrorists hideouts, troops of 155 Task Force Battalion conducted a patrol to Nimila village and rescued 14 persons from the clutches of Boko Haram terrorists. Some weapons were also recovered. A statement from the Acting Director, Army Public Relations, Col Sani Usman said, the rescued persons were mostly women and children. The troops also recovered 3 Dane guns, a single barrel and 2 double barrels. Also recovered were 3 motor cycles abandoned by the terrorists, in addition to 2 mobile phones.